# 📍 Day 9 — Storage Overview, Classes & FSx

## 🎯 Objective

Understand AWS storage services and choose the right one based on performance, cost, and use case.

---

## 📦 Storage Types in AWS

### 🔹 S3 (Object Storage)

* Scalable and durable
* Used for files, backups, static content

---

### 🔹 EBS (Block Storage)

* Attached to EC2
* High performance
* Persistent storage

---

### 🔹 EFS (File Storage)

* Shared across multiple EC2 instances
* Automatically scalable

---

### 🔹 FSx (Managed File Systems)

* Fully managed file systems
* Types:

  * FSx for Windows File Server
  * FSx for Lustre
  * FSx for NetApp ONTAP
  * FSx for OpenZFS

---

## 📂 S3 Storage Classes

* **Standard** → frequent access
* **Standard-IA** → infrequent access
* **Glacier** → archival storage
* **Intelligent-Tiering** → automatic tiering

---

## ⚖️ Storage Comparison

| Storage | Type               | Use Case             |
| ------- | ------------------ | -------------------- |
| S3      | Object             | Files, backups       |
| EBS     | Block              | EC2 storage          |
| EFS     | File               | Shared systems       |
| FSx     | File (specialized) | Enterprise workloads |

---

## 💡 Key Learnings

* Different storage types solve different problems
* FSx is used for **specialized enterprise workloads**
* S3 classes help optimize cost

---

## 🚧 Challenges Faced

* Differentiating EFS vs FSx
* Understanding when to use which storage

